row.value: The total count of inbound calls arriving in the contact center. Helpful Info: Includes calls arriving in an IVR and terminating prior to being offered to an agent queue as well as all calls offered to agent queues. For contact centers with an IVR, these calls are typically started in the IVR, but it is possible to have some calls bypass the IVR and those calls are also counted as calls created. If there is not an IVR, then Calls Created should be the number of calls that were offered to agents queues. Data Source: ACD

The count of calls created that terminated in the IVR prior to being offered to an agent queue. Helpful info: If there is an IVR, Calls Created - Calls Offered = Calls Contained in IVR. Data Source: ACD

The total count of inbound calls that were sent to agent queues. Helpful Info: includes calls which were terminated prior to being handled by an agent (abandoned). Typically Calls Offered is measured by count of calls that were routed by the ACD to all agent queues. Data Source: ACD

The total count of inbound calls offered that were also answered by an agent, regardless of the outcome or length of the call. Helpful Info: Does not include calls terminated prior to reaching an agent. Example: a call answered by an agent resulting in a hang-up by the caller after only a few seconds would be counted as a call handled. Likewise, a call answered by an agent and then transferred would also be counted as a call handled. Data Source: ACD
The total count of web chats arriving in the contact center. This includes web chats terminated prior to being offered to an agent as well as all web chats offered to agents. Data Source: ACD
The total count of web chats created that were also answered by an agent, regardless of the outcome or length of the web chat. Data Source: ACD

The number of seconds representing the average length of time that agents spent working a call from the time the call is answered by an agent to the time the call is terminated. This includes talk time, after call work time and hold time. Formula: Average Handle Time = (Talk Time Total + Hold Time Total + After Call Work Time Total) / Calls Handled Data Source: ACD

The number of seconds representing the longest length of time that an agent spend working a call from the time the call was answered to the time the call was terminated (handle time). Data Source: ACD

The number of seconds representing the average length of time that inbound calls were waiting in a queue prior being answered by an agent. Helpful Info: Does not include web chat or voicemail Data Source: ACD
The maximum wait time (in seconds) of a single caller before reaching an agent during the specified timeframe. Data Source: ACD

The percentage of inbound phone calls made to a call center or service desk that are abandoned in the queue by the customer before speaking to a live CSR agent. Helpful Info: An abandoned call is a call or other type of contact initiated to a call center that is ended before any conversation occurs. The call is terminated before being answered by agent. Abandon rates have a direct relation to waiting times. The longer the time that customers have to wait before being connected to an agent, the higher the abandon rate is likely to be. Formula: AB Rate = Abandoned calls/ Calls offered *100. Data Source: ACD

The percentage of the total calls offered for the entire reporting period for the single day with the highest number of calls offered. Example: collect the count of calls offered for each day of the reporting period. If the day with the highest number has calls offered of 2,900, and the total number of calls offered during the reporting period is 12,000, then the peak day percentage is 2,900/12,000 = 24%. Data Source: ACD

The percentage of the total calls offered for the entire reporting period for the single week with the highest number of calls offered. Example: collect the count of calls offered for each week of the reporting period. If the week with the highest number has calls offered of 12,300 and the total number of calls offered during the entire reporting period is 35,000, then the peak week percentage is 12,300/35,000 = 35% Data Source: ACD
The total number of documents sent by MAXIMUS to consumers/applicants/enrollees (all channels).
The total number of documents sent by MAXIMUS to consumers/applicants/enrollees via mail and/or fax.
The total number of documents sent by MAXIMUS to consumers/applicants/enrollees via email.
The total number of documents sent/posted by MAXIMUS to consumers/applicants/enrollees via electronic accounts/portals.
